        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "type": "text",
          "variant": "subheading",
          "style": {
            "padding_top": 3,
            "padding_bottom": 3
          },
          "heading_html": "<p>By the end of this module, you will be able to:</p>"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "type": "list",
          "variant": "bulleted",
          "style": {
            "padding_top": 3,
            "padding_bottom": 3
          },
          "list_style": "bulleted",
          "items_html": [
            "<p>Explain the transition to ORW and its impact on AI efficiency and scalability. &nbsp;</p>",
            "<p>Identify ORW anatomy, payload options, compatibility, and sustainability features. &nbsp;</p>",
            "<p>Define power integrity, 100A sequencing, and the High Power Rack shared baseline.</p>"
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "type": "divider",
          "variant": "divider",
          "style": {
            "padding_top": 3,
            "padding_bottom": 3
          }
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "type": "text",
          "variant": "paragraph",
          "style": {
            "padding_top": 3,
            "padding_bottom": 3
          },
          "body_html": "<p>As the demands of AI accelerate, the standard 600 millimeter rack creates a severe<strong> physical bottleneck</strong>. This module explores how the OCP community &nbsp;is responding with the 1200 millimeter ORW frame.</p><p>You will learn how the standard is evolving to meet next-generation requirements through smarter power delivery, robust structural designs, and scalable infrastructure.</p>"
        },
        {
          "id": 6,
          "type": "image",
          "variant": "hero",
          "style": {
            "image_size": "large",
            "image_opacity": 0.5,
            "image_opacity_color": "#000000",
            "zoom_on_click": true,
