    {
      "id": 5,
      "slug": "orw-power-shelves-busbar",
      "title": "ORW Power Shelves & Busbar",
      "description_html": "",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "type": "image",
          "variant": "full",
          "style": {
            "background_type": "LIGHT",
            "card_mode": "WHITE",
            "image_opacity": 0.5,
            "image_opacity_color": "#000000",
            "zoom_on_click": false,
            "attached_to_next": false,
            "padding_top": 0,
            "padding_bottom": 0,
            "custom_padding_top": 0,
            "custom_padding_bottom": 0,
            "entrance_animation": true
          },
          "image_role": "decorative",
          "media": {
            "path": "resources/images/black-banner-intro.png",
            "alt": "Black banner - intro.png",
            "source_asset": "Black banner - intro.png",
            "mime_type": "image/png",
            "bytes": 12283,
            "dimensions": {
              "originalWidth": 1680,
              "originalHeight": 295
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "type": "text",
          "variant": "paragraph",
          "style": {
            "background_type": "COLOR",
            "background_color": "#1e1e1e",
            "attached_to_next": false,
            "padding_top": 3,
            "padding_bottom": 3
          },
          "body_html": "<p>Delivering power to a high-density AI rack requires robust electrical connections. The ORW frame uses standardized interfaces to mount the 48V busbar, ensuring seamless interoperability with High Power Rack shared baselines.</p><p>Click on each tab to learn more.</p>"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "type": "accordion",
          "variant": "accordion",
          "style": {
            "background_type": "COLOR",
            "background_color": "#1e1e1e",
            "zoom_on_click": false,
            "attached_to_next": false,
            "padding_top": 3,
            "padding_bottom": 3
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "title": "Standardized Busbar Mounting",
              "description_html": "<p>The frame interfaces for busbar mounting are identical to ORV3 HPR busbar interfaces.</p>",
              "media": {
                "path": "resources/images/untitled-design-49.jpg",
                "alt": "Untitled design (49).png",
                "source_asset": "Untitled design (49).jpg",
                "mime_type": "image/jpeg",
                "bytes": 100049,
                "dimensions": {
                  "width": 1680,
                  "height": 944,
                  "originalWidth": 1680,
                  "originalHeight": 1680
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "title": "100A Continuous Power Path",
              "description_html": "<p>The  IT Gear Input Connector features a primary power path and a power return path that are both rated for a minimum of 100A continuous current.</p>",
              "media": {
                "path": "resources/images/untitled-design-50.jpg",
                "alt": "Untitled design (50).png",
                "source_asset": "Untitled design (50).jpg",
                "mime_type": "image/jpeg",
                "bytes": 38421,
                "dimensions": {
                  "originalWidth": 1680,
                  "originalHeight": 1680
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "title": "Power Sequencing & Sensing",
              "description_html": "<p>The new connector requires IT gear designs to use the power sense line to control the on and off behavior of power entry circuitry, preventing dangerous arcing events.</p>",
              "media": {
                "path": "resources/images/it-gear-input-connector.png",
                "alt": "IT Gear Input Connector.png",
                "source_asset": "IT Gear Input Connector.png",
                "mime_type": "image/png",
                "bytes": 33471,
                "dimensions": {
                  "originalWidth": 541,
                  "originalHeight": 512
                }
              }
            },
            {
              "title": "Differential Voltage Sensing",
              "description_html": "<p>This optional but highly recommended feature allows facilities to monitor the voltage drop of the input power cable assembly, enhancing thermal event mitigation.</p>"
            }
          ]
        },
