    {
      "id": 6,
      "slug": "knowledge-check",
      "title": "Knowledge Check",
      "description_html": "",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "type": "text",
          "variant": "paragraph",
          "style": {
            "attached_to_next": false,
            "padding_top": 3,
            "padding_bottom": 3
          },
          "body_html": "<p style=\"line-height: 1.94118\"><span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-decoration: inherit\" data-color-scope=\"outer\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255)\"><span>Test your knowledge from this module. Select the best answer for each question, then submit.</span></span></span></span></p>"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "type": "image",
          "variant": "full",
          "style": {
            "background_type": "LIGHT",
            "card_mode": "WHITE",
            "image_opacity": 0.5,
            "image_opacity_color": "#000000",
            "zoom_on_click": false,
            "attached_to_next": false,
            "padding_top": 0,
            "padding_bottom": 0,
            "custom_padding_top": 0,
            "custom_padding_bottom": 0,
            "entrance_animation": true
          },
          "image_role": "decorative",
          "media": {
            "path": "resources/images/black-banner-intro-1.png",
            "alt": "Black banner - intro.png",
            "source_asset": "Black banner - intro-1.png",
            "mime_type": "image/png",
            "bytes": 12283,
            "dimensions": {
              "originalWidth": 1680,
              "originalHeight": 295
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "type": "knowledge_check",
          "variant": "multiple_choice",
          "style": {
            "background_type": "COLOR",
            "background_color": "#1e1e1e",
            "attached_to_next": false,
            "padding_top": 3,
            "padding_bottom": 3
          },
          "question_type": "multiple_choice",
          "question_html": "<p>Why does the ORW base specification eliminate standard rolling casters from the rack design?</p>",
          "choices": [
            {
              "text_html": "<p>To make room for larger liquid cooling manifolds.</p>",
              "correct": false
            },
            {
              "text_html": "<p>To safely support weights up to 3,500 kilograms directly on structural platforms.</p>",
              "correct": true
            },
            {
              "text_html": "<p>To ensure compatibility with older 19-inch IT gear.</p>",
              "correct": false
            },
            {
              "text_html": "<p>To reduce the overall manufacturing cost of the base frame.</p>",
              "correct": false
            }
          ],
          "feedback_correct_html": "<p>Correct! Because a fully loaded ORW rack can weigh 3,500 kilograms, standard casters are no longer a safe option. The rack sits directly on structural platforms for maximum stability.</p>",
          "feedback_incorrect_html": "<p>Standard casters would buckle under the massive 3,500 kilogram weight of a populated AI cluster. The ORW frame is designed to sit directly on structural platforms.</p>"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "type": "knowledge_check",
          "variant": "multiple_choice",
          "style": {
            "background_type": "COLOR",
            "background_color": "#1e1e1e",
            "attached_to_next": false,
            "padding_top": 3,
            "padding_bottom": 3
          },
          "question_type": "multiple_choice",
          "question_html": "<p>True or False? The Open Rack Wide frame only supports OpenU vertical spacing.</p>",
          "choices": [
            {
              "text_html": "<p>True</p>",
              "correct": false
            },
            {
              "text_html": "<p>False</p>",
              "correct": true
            }
          ],
          "feedback_correct_html": "<p>Correct! The ORW frame supports both OU and RU vertical spacing. It includes specific cutouts for support brackets to allow the mixing of various types of IT equipment.</p>",
          "feedback_incorrect_html": "<p>Incorrect. The base specification mandates that the ORW frame must support both OU and RU vertical spacing through varying support brackets.</p>"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "type": "knowledge_check",
          "variant": "multiple_choice",
          "style": {
            "background_type": "COLOR",
            "background_color": "#1e1e1e",
            "attached_to_next": false,
            "padding_top": 3,
            "padding_bottom": 3
          },
          "question_type": "multiple_choice",
          "question_html": "<p>What is the minimum continuous current rating for the primary power and return paths on the Open Rack V3 IT Gear Input Connector?</p>",
          "choices": [
            {
              "text_html": "<p>200A continuous</p>",
              "correct": false
            },
            {
              "text_html": "<p>150A continuous</p>",
              "correct": false
            },
            {
              "text_html": "<p>100A continuous</p>",
              "correct": true
            },
            {
              "text_html": "<p>50A continuous</p>",
              "correct": false
            }
          ],
          "feedback_correct_html": "<p>Correct! Both the power path and the power return path on the input connector must be rated for a minimum of 100A continuous current.</p>",
          "feedback_incorrect_html": "<p>Incorrect. The input connector requires a minimum rating of 100A continuous for both the primary power and power return paths.</p>"
        },
        {
          "id": 6,
          "type": "image",
          "variant": "full",
          "style": {
            "background_type": "LIGHT",
            "card_mode": "WHITE",
            "image_opacity": 0.5,
            "image_opacity_color": "#000000",
            "zoom_on_click": false,
            "attached_to_next": false,
